"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: Add `kiroAgent.trustedCommands` to `.vscode/settings.json` during Kiro enable\n\n## Context\n\nWhen `entire enable` installs Kiro hooks, the IDE hook files (`.kiro/hooks/*.kiro.hook`) run shell commands like `entire hooks kiro stop`. The Kiro IDE requires these commands to be explicitly trusted via `kiroAgent.trustedCommands` in `.vscode/settings.json`, otherwise the user gets prompted for approval on every hook invocation. This change makes `entire enable` automatically configure this trust setting.\n\n## Files to modify\n\n1. **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks.go`** — Add trusted commands logic to `InstallHooks`, `UninstallHooks`, idempotency check, and `AreHooksInstalled`\n2. **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks_test.go`** — Add tests for the new behavior\n\n## Implementation\n\n### 1. Add constants and helpers in `hooks.go`\n\n- Add `vscodeSettingsDir = \".vscode\"` and `vscodeSettingsFile = \"settings.json\"` constants\n- Add `trustedCommandsKey = \"kiroAgent.trustedCommands\"` constant\n- Add `prodTrustedCommand = \"entire hooks *\"` constant\n- Add `localDevTrustedCommand = \"go run ${KIRO_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks *\"` constant (or just use localDevCmdPrefix + \"hooks *\" dynamically)\n\n### 2. Update `InstallHooks` in `hooks.go`\n\nAfter installing CLI + IDE hooks, also:\n- Read `.vscode/settings.json` using raw `map[string]json.RawMessage` to preserve unknown fields (same pattern as Claude Code's `hooks.go`)\n- Parse `kiroAgent.trustedCommands` as `[]string`\n- Check if the appropriate trusted command pattern is already present (`\"entire hooks *\"` for prod, local-dev prefix + `\"hooks *\"` for local-dev)\n- If not present, append it and write back\n- Return count should NOT change (trusted commands are a side effect, not hooks themselves)\n\n### 3. Update idempotency check in `InstallHooks`\n\nThe early-return check at line 76-81 currently verifies `allHooksPresent && allIDEHooksPresent`. Add `trustedCommandsPresent(worktreeRoot, localDev)` to this check so that if the trusted command is missing (but hooks exist), it still proceeds with the install.\n\n### 4. Update `UninstallHooks` in `hooks.go`\n\nAfter removing CLI agent file and IDE hook files:\n- Read `.vscode/settings.json`\n- Remove the `\"entire hooks *\"` and local-dev variant from `kiroAgent.trustedCommands` array\n- If the array becomes empty, remove the key entirely\n- If the settings object becomes empty, remove the file (or leave it — safer to leave it since other settings may exist)\n- Preserve all other settings in the file\n\n### 5. Update `AreHooksInstalled` (no change needed)\n\nThe current logic checks CLI or IDE hooks. The trusted commands setting is supplementary — hooks are \"installed\" based on the hook files, not the trust setting. No change needed here.\n\n### 6. Add tests in `hooks_test.go`\n\n- `TestInstallHooks_CreatesTrustedCommands` — fresh install creates `.vscode/settings.json` with correct trusted command\n- `TestInstallHooks_TrustedCommands_PreservesExistingSettings` — existing `.vscode/settings.json` with other settings is preserved\n- `TestInstallHooks_TrustedCommands_LocalDevMode` — local-dev mode uses the local-dev prefix pattern\n- `TestInstallHooks_TrustedCommands_Idempotent` — second install doesn't duplicate the entry\n- `TestInstallHooks_TrustedCommands_PreservesExistingTrustedCommands` — existing user-added trusted commands are preserved\n- `TestUninstallHooks_RemovesTrustedCommands` — uninstall removes the entry\n- `TestUninstallHooks_TrustedCommands_PreservesOtherSettings` — other settings remain after uninstall\n- `TestUninstallHooks_TrustedCommands_PreservesUserTrustedCommands` — user's other trusted commands survive uninstall\n\n## Key design decisions\n\n- **Round-trip preservation**: Use `map[string]json.RawMessage` to preserve unknown VS Code settings (same pattern as Claude Code's `hooks.go` lines 62-94)\n- **Trusted command pattern**: `\"entire hooks *\"` covers all hook verbs with a single wildcard entry\n- **Idempotency**: Check before adding; don't duplicate entries\n- **Don't modify hook count**: The return value from `InstallHooks` counts hooks, not settings changes — trusted commands are an ancillary configuration\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\n```\n\nSpecifically verify:\n- `go test ./cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/ -run TestInstallHooks_CreatesTrustedCommands -v`\n- `go test ./cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/ -run TestUninstallHooks_RemovesTrustedCommands -v`\n- Full test suite passes: `mise run test:ci`\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-wt-kiro-oneshot/3962da63-dcfe-4785-8e7e-ad2a32b724d5.jsonl\n\n---\n\ngetting this error again from kiro ide Run Command Hook\n\nentire-prompt-submit\nCommand timed out with no output captured.\n\n---\n\n[Request interrupted by user for tool use]"